{
  "stem": "17.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 68.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But that was his idea, the Zionist, early Zionism.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Unfortunately, it didn't work out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And after a year he came back losing all the hope and also the money that he planned to invest there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, that's what I wanted to mention.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember I had a lot being in school with Catholic girls, with Polish girls.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was a girl's school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had many friends.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some were even very close.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I trusted them to the point when once I was in their house and her older sister came from the university wearing the insignia of the anti-Semitic party.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that made me almost sick.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Of course, I didn't tell anything at home because that was what my family expected.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I know I was crying the whole night.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was probably one of the first disappointments.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And, still, that was my dilemma, to continue friendship with this girl which was very sweet and good friend and taking position, which, as a child, it was very difficult for me.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So that was the first dilemma.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I had much more experiences later when I was invited to a party to my Christian friends, and sometimes I was the only one Jewish girl, sometimes another one.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And there were people from a different school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They didn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I didn't look Jewish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And after a while, after a short time, started a conversation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And, of course, the subject was very unpleasant to me, that was sarcastic towards Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I didn't know what to do, if I should leave or put my position or just ignore it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So I was avoiding this as I grew up.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
